TY  - JOUR
AU  - Newbery, David M. G.
AU  - Stiglitz, Joseph E.
T1  - Risk Aversion, Supply Response, and the Optimality of Random Prices: A Diagrammatic Analysis*
PY  - 1982
Y1  - 1982/02/01
DO  - 10.2307/1882624
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 97
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 26
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper analyzes the effect of commodity price stabilization on producers and consumers, both in the short run, and in the long run, when producers have adjusted their production decisions to take account of the change in the price distribution. We derive conditions under which (a) both producers and consumers may be better off; and (b) both producers and consumers may be worse off. Moreover, we show that the long-run effects may differ not only quantitatively but also qualitatively from the short-run effects. The anomalous results may occur even with reasonable assumptions concerning production functions and utility functions of producers and consumers.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1882624
ER  - 



